  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\ncurrently, the `env` `tx` are using the `gas_price` from the fork `eth_gasprice`,\r\n\r\nshould we instead use the config `gas_price`?\r\n\r\nthis gas_price is always present which makes it difficult to detect whether the user modified the gas_price, only by comparing to the default `gas_price`.\r\n\r\nalways using the config gas price, would also break some assumptions I think, so not entirely sure what to do here.\r\n\r\nmost practical, would be to use the user defined `gasprice` if it deviates from the `Config::default` perhaps?\r\n\r\nor we make `gasPrice` and Option<u64>, which would require some additional code changes\r\n\r\nwdyt @gakonst @onbjerg \n\n### Additional context\n\nref #1383\r\n\r\n>Hello,\r\nI just fetched the newest forge and it seems that the gas_price parameter in foundry.toml is ignored. Current mainnet gas price is used instead.\r\n\r\n>My foundry.toml:\r\n\r\n`\r\n[default]\r\nsrc = 'src'\r\nout = 'out'\r\nlibs = ['lib']\r\nremappings = ['ds-test/=lib/ds-test/src/', 'forge-std/=lib/forge-std/src/']\r\neth-rpc-url = 'RPC_URL'\r\nfork_block_number = 14411926\r\ngas_price = 40000000000\r\n`\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @benesjan in https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/1383#issuecomment-1125218989_",
